  "text": "where D train (y i ) is the i th training response output data,ŷ i the prediction of the training data made by N k , s 2 k is the variance of prediction error e ki , and N the number of samples in the training data. The prediction error e ki measured is considered to be a random sample from a normal distribution with a mean µ of zero and variance s 2 k . Using the principle of maximum likelihood estimation (MLE) (see [CITATION_1] ), the variance s 2 k for N k can be estimated as:",
